  "base_commit": "b313b6412b4fb382fe16471c7c437cc053290477",
  "pr_number": 10277,
  "issue_number": 10273,
  "issue_title": "EventDispatcher leaks memory via `_outbound_buffer` after broker reconnection (gevent pool)",
  "issue_body": "# Checklist\n\n- [x] I have verified that the issue exists against the `main` branch of Celery.\n- [x] I have read the relevant section in the\n  [contribution guide](https://docs.celeryq.dev/en/main/contributing.html#other-bugs)\n  on reporting bugs.\n- [x] I have checked the [issues list](https://github.com/celery/celery/issues?q=is%3Aissue+label%3A%22Issue+Type%3A+Bug+Report%22+-label%3A%22Category%3A+Documentation%22)\n  for similar or identical bug reports.\n- [x] I have checked the [pull requests list](https://github.com/celery/celery/pulls?q=is%3Apr+label%3A%22PR+Type%3A+Bugfix%22+-label%3A%22Category%3A+Documentation%22)\n  for existing proposed fixes.\n- [x] I have checked the [commit log](https://github.com/celery/celery/commits/main)\n  to find out if the bug was already fixed in the main branch.\n- [x] I have included all related issues and possible duplicate issues\n  in this issue (If there are none, check this box anyway).\n\n## Mandatory Debugging Information\n\n- [x] I have included the output of ``celery -A proj report`` in the issue.\n    (if you are not able to do this, then at least specify the Celery\n     version affected).\n- [x] I have verified that the issue exists against the `main` branch of Celery.\n- [x] I have included the contents of ``pip freeze`` in the issue.\n- [x] I have included all the versions of all the external dependencies required\n  to reproduce this bug.\n\n## Related Issues and Possible Duplicates\n\n#### Related Issues\n\n- #5047\n\n#### Possible Duplicates\n\n- None\n\n## Environment & Settings\n\n**Celery version**: 5.6.3\n\n<details>\n<summary><b><code>celery report</code> Output:</b></summary>\n<p>\n\n```\nsoftware -> celery:5.6.3 (dawn-chorus) kombu:5.6.2 py:3.14.0\n            billiard:4.2.4 py-amqp:5.3.1\nplatform -> system:Linux arch:64bit, ELF\n            kernel version:6.1.134-153.879.amzn2023.x86_64\nloader   -> celery.loaders.app.AppLoader\nsettings -> transport:amqps result:N/A\n\nbroker_url: amqps://***:***@***:5671/socra_ai\ndeprecated_settings: None\n```\n\n</p>\n</details>\n\n# Steps to Reproduce\n\n## Required Dependencies\n\n- **Minimal Python Version**: 3.11\n- **Minimal Celery Version**: 5.4\n- **Minimal Kombu Version**: 5.6.2\n- **Minimal Broker Version**: RabbitMQ 3\n- **Minimal Result Backend Version**: N/A\n- **Minimal OS and/or Kernel Version**: N/A\n- **Minimal Broker Client Version**: amqp 5.3.1\n- **Minimal Result Backend Client Version**: N/A\n\n### Python Packages\n\n<details>\n<summary><b><code>pip freeze</code> Output:</b></summary>\n<p>\n\n```\namqp==5.3.1\nbilliard==4.2.4\ncelery==5.6.3\nclick==8.3.2\nclick-didyoumean==0.3.1\nclick-plugins==1.1.1.2\nclick-repl==0.3.0\ngevent==26.4.0\ngreenlet==3.4.0\nkombu==5.6.2\npackaging==26.1\nprompt-toolkit==3.0.52\npsutil==7.2.2\npython-dateutil==2.9.0.post0\nsix==1.17.0\ntzdata==2026.1\ntzlocal==5.3.1\nvine==5.1.0\nwcwidth==0.6.0\nzope-event==6.1\nzope-interface==8.3\n```\n\n</p>\n</details>\n\n### Other Dependencies\n\n<details>\n<p>\nDocker (for RabbitMQ container)\n</p>\n</details>\n\n## Minimally Reproducible Test Case\n\n<details>\n<p>\n\nhttps://github.com/JaeHyuckSa/celery-gevent-memory-leak-issue\n\n```bash\nuv sync\nuv run python main.py\n```\n\n</p>\n</details>\n\n# Expected Behavior\n\nAfter broker reconnection, the old `EventDispatcher` should stop its heartbeat timer or guard against `producer=None`, so no objects accumulate in `_outbound_buffer`.\n\n# Actual Behavior\n\nWhen the broker connection drops and reconnects, the old `EventDispatcher`'s heartbeat timer keeps calling `_publish()` with `producer=None`.\n\nhttps://github.com/celery/celery/blob/main/celery/events/dispatcher.py#L142-L160\n\n```python\ntry:\n    producer.publish(...)\nexcept Exception as exc:\n    if not self.buffer_while_offline:\n        raise\n    self._outbound_buffer.append((event, routing_key, exc))\n```\n\n`producer` is `None`, so `producer.publish()` raises `AttributeError`. `_publish()` catches it and appends `(event, routing_key, exc)` to `_outbound_buffer`. The exception keeps traceback/frame references alive, so they never get GC'd. This repeats every ~2s.",
